    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, **Vinnie Pasquantino** (76.21) and **Corbin Carroll** (75.04) anchor the Ghost Ride the WHIP lineup as our primary producers. **Vinnie Pasquantino** benefits from a significant SP skill bump against L. Severino, compounded by a park factor boost and the high-leverage utility of the #3 spot in the order. Meanwhile, **Corbin Carroll** remains an essential start; despite a modest park factor, his elite projected xwOBA (.372) and favorable platoon advantage against Sproat ensure he remains our most consistent engine for the scarcity-heavy categories of HR and SB. **Josh Naylor** also earns a strong recommendation (72.22) thanks to the combination of a favorable SP matchup against T. Bradley and the inherent RBI potential of batting cleanup.\n\nOur most critical bench decision involved **Alex Freeland**, who fell just short of a starting berth with a score of 51.51. While **Alex Freeland** offers switch-hitting versatility and positive wind indicators, he was ultimately eclipsed by the superior efficiency metrics of **Dalton Rushing** and **Kyle Karros**. Specifically, **Kyle Karros** (63.78) surged into the lineup due to a high SP skill disparity against Williamson and favorable wind conditions that provide a non-trivial boost to his power profile. Conversely, we are keeping **Austin Riley** (43.75) and **Jose Caballero** (39.32) on the pine to protect our daily game cap efficiency; **Austin Riley** faces the elite arm of Skubal, and **Jose Caballero**'s projection was dragged down significantly by a negative platoon split against Eovaldi.\n\nRisk management remains paramount today, particularly with **Vinnie Pasquantino** currently listed as \"Lineup Pending.\" While our projections assume him in the #3 hole, any shift down the order or a late scratch could alter his efficiency score. Additionally, while **Mickey Moniak** (56.32) and **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** (52.10) are active, their scores are dampened by significant platoon disadvantages\u2014**Mickey Moniak** specifically suffers a 15% drop against left-handed pitching. We are closely monitoring the weather at the Williamson matchup, where the \"Wind Out\" warning provides the only real cushion for our lower-ranked starters.",
